    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Strings are <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/essential/concurrency/immutable.html\">immutable objects</a> so you can copy them just coping the reference to them, because the object  referenced can't change ... </p>\n\n<p>So you can copy as in your first example without any problem : </p>\n\n<pre><code>String s = \"hello\";\nString backup_of_s = s;\ns = \"bye\";\n</code></pre>\n"
